underlying_goal: To commit a large number of new documentation and spec files, create a pull request, merge it, and update the main branch.
friction_detail: A brief moment of confusion where the user asked to push to main after a PR was already created, which Claude correctly interpreted as a request to merge the PR and update the main branch.
primary_success: Efficiently handled a multi-step Git workflow: creating a branch, committing numerous files, creating a pull request, merging it, and cleaning up, all through tool calls.
brief_summary: The user requested to commit and push a large number of untracked documentation and specification files. Claude created a new branch, committed the files, created a pull request, and upon clarification, merged the pull request and updated the main branch, completing the entire deployment workflow.
